DISABLED-PARENTS _ Ken and Mary are mildly mentally retarded,
adults whose minds are more like those of young teenagers. They
have become a rare success story, a tribute to an era that is bec
oming more enlightened about the needs and abilities of the
developmentally disabled. With the help of a consultant supplied by
the state Department of Economic Security, they face the challenges
of rearing two adolescent boys. By KARINA BLAND. Story will move in
