r s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-BBN-DODGERS-NOTES-LAD     05-16 0427
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BBN-DODGERS-NOTES-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
SHEFFIELD BREAKS .300 MARK
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By MATT McHALE  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   ST. LOUIS _ Gary Sheffield, who missed most of spring training
with pain in his surgically repaired right shoulder, had three more
hits Saturday, moving his average over .300 for the first time this
season.
</P>
<P>
   Sheffield doubled and scored in the fourth and doubled home Eric
Young in the fifth inning of the Dodgers' 8-5 loss to the St. Louis
Cardinals. He also singled home Young in the ninth.
</P>
<P>
   It was his club-leading 14th multi-hit game of the season and
extended his hitting streak to seven games (12 for 28 over that
period). He also has hit in 10 of his last 11 (18 for 45), raising
his average to .308 (41 for 133).
</P>
<P>
   And though he wasn't pleased with his move to left field in
spring training, Sheffield hasn't committed an error in 35 games
this season.
</P>
<P>
   Grudzielanek wakes up: After three days on the bench last week,
Mark Grudzielanek appears to finally be stirring offensively. For
the second consecutive night, Grudzielanek had two hits and his
fourth-inning single scored Raul Mondesi to give the Dodgers a 3-1
lead.
</P>
<P>
   Dodgers manager Davey Johnson went with Jose Vizcaino at short
after Grudzielanek opened the season with just two hits in 33
at-bats with runners in scoring position.
</P>
<P>
   ``This is a slow process, but I think I'm coming out of it,''
Grudzielanek said. ``In Montreal, I worked out of things by
playing. I don't know if taking a couple of days off will really
help.''
</P>
<P>
   Dreifort to miss start: With an off-day Monday, Johnson expects
to skip fifth starter Darren Dreifort in the rotation. Dreifort,
who had a no decision in last Wednesday's 3-2 victory over Chicago,
has been bothered by a sprained right ankle.
</P>
<P>
   By skipping Dreifort, Kevin Brown will pitch Thursday night
against Houston at Dodger Stadium.
</P>
<P>
   ``His leg isn't that serious,'' pitching coach Charlie Hough
said of Dreifort. ``It is more of a precaution.''
</P>
<P>
   Suggestion: Third base coach Rick Dempsey is an old friend of
Angels struggling right-hander Tim Belcher dating back to their
seasons with the Dodgers a decade ago. Dempsey has watched Belcher
struggle this season and called him Saturday morning after Belcher
defeated Tampa Bay on Friday night.
</P>
<P>
   ``He is still pretty grumpy about the whole thing so I just hung
up,'' Dempsey said. ``I know what he's doing wrong. I keep telling
him, `Show me your number.' He has to turn his body more during his
windup.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
