<HEADLINE>
CHARISMATIC EARNS SHOT AT CROWN 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By MICHAEL MADDEN  
 c.1999 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   BALTIMORE _ And now the improbable of all thoroughbred
improbables _ a claiming horse winning the Triple Crown. It's
possible, if not likely. Secretariat just may be tossing in his
grave.
</P>
<P>
   Charismatic, unloved, unrespected, and unbelievable, Saturday
swooped where no horse at Pimlico Race Course has swooped in the
last few days, on the far outside of a track that has had an
extreme inside bias, and easily, comfortably, and convincingly won
the 124th Preakness before a record crowd of 100,311.
</P>
<P>
   Now it is on to Belmont Park for Charismatic and a shot to win
the Triple Crown, something no colt has accomplished since Affirmed
in 1978. It's the third straight year a 3-year-old has a chance to
do it: Real Quiet missed by a nose last year and Silver Charm
failed by less than a length in 1997.
</P>
<P>
   Twenty-eight horses have won the first two jewels of the Triple
Crown, but only 11 have been up to American racing's greatest
challenge. And D. Wayne Lukas, Charismatic's trainer, has felt for
weeks that it would be the Belmont Stakes where Charismatic would
run his best.
</P>
<P>
   ``I told (owners) Bob and Beverly Lewis before the Derby, back
in March, that I didn't know about the Derby and I didn't know
about the Preakness, but that I'm looking forward to the Belmont,''
said Lukas. ``It's his style of running. Now the monkey is really
on my back. I said we've got a Belmont horse and now we've got to
prove it.''
</P>
<P>
   Dismissed at 31-1 in Louisville, ignored at 8-1 Saturday,
Charismatic now will be certain to go off as the favorite in three
weeks at New York. A truly amazing tale for a horse who twice was
entered in claiming races _ racing's blue-collar basement _ and now
is only a mile and a half from greatness.
</P>
<P>
   Not since 1953, when Dark Star upset Native Dancer, one of the
great horses of the century, has a Kentucky Derby winner gone off
at such high odds in the Preakness. Dark Star was 11-1 in the
Preakness (won by Native Dancer); Charismatic's 8-1 odds were the
second highest for a Derby winner in Baltimore.
</P>
<P>
   In recent years, Lukas had slipped out of the spotlight, which
he so loves, as trainer Bob Baffert garnered media attention
everywhere. But now he's back in the limelight, having won the
Derby, Preakness, and Belmont 12 times ``except, I've never won all
three with the same horse,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   When Lukas walked onto the Preakness track with Charismatic
prior to the race, he told jockey Chris Antley: ``He's as ready as
human hands can make him.'' And when the race was done, Charismatic
home by a most comfortable 1 1/2 lengths, Lukas pointed to the
watch on his arm and told the tale of how he had bought it 14 years
ago.
</P>
<P>
   It's a Triple Crown watch and each of the hour hands has the
silks of the 11 previous winners, said the trainer. ``But there are
no silks for 12 o'clock high,'' said Lukas. ``I just want to see
the green-and-white colors (of Charismatic) for 12 o'clock high.''
</P>
<P>
   Charismatic paid 18.80 to win as he easily disposed of Menifee,
the 2-1 favorite, completing a generous perfecta of $47.60 for the
same finish as the Derby. Badge, a 58-1 outsider almost caught
Menifee for place, completing a $2,049 trifecta.
</P>
<P>
   The two most disappointing horses in the race were Godolphin
Stable's Worldly Manner, which was able to reach fourth on the far
turn but retreated to finish 35 lengths back, and the filly
Excellent Meeting. Her trainer, Baffert, had talked her up all week
but she was pulled up in distress with breathing problems before
the final turn and was walked off the track.
</P>
<P>
   ``I thought I might have pulled the trigger too soon,'' said Pat
Day, the jockey on Menifee, ``and then in the far turn I got in a
little tight and lost my position briefly.'' And, in his most
significant words, Day added, ``We got near the winner but we
couldn't make up any ground in the last 16th.''
</P>
<P>
   For sure, Charismatic would have no worries from Menifee at
Belmont and, of the horses he trounced Saturday, only Badge and
Stephen Got Even seem to be threats. As usual, though, there are
any number of newcomers, as many as 12 new steeds, who are
considering Belmont.
</P>
<P>
   But it is not that Charismatic won the Preakness that was
impressive, it was the way he won it. It had been next to
impossible to be on the outside of the Pimlico track for days, as
the horse closest to the rail benefited in race after race. And as
the early races Saturday at Pimlico were run, friends came to Lukas
and alerted him.
</P>
<P>
   But if the inside were the place to be, ``We weren't going to be
there,'' said Lukas. He could not change his horse's style now and
he wasn't going to tell Antley to ride any differently. ``We were
going to have to close from the outside,'' said Lukas. ``In
basketball, if you press, then when you get to a big game, you
press. In football, if you run off tackle, then you run off
tackle.''
</P>
<P>
   Charismatic pressed, Charismatic ran, and Charismatic now can
claim greatness after nobody claimed him for $62,500.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
