 Sunday, May 16, 1999      The Hearst News Service will file this story for Monday:
<TEXT>
<P>
   WAL-MART-VERDICT (San Antonio) _ A jury here has awarded a
Mexican company more than $624 million after finding Wal-Mart and a
Wal-Mart subsidiary acted with malice when it broke a partnership
deal to distribute groceries throughout Mexico. On Monday, jurors
will return to court to decide whether Wal-Mart and its subsidiary
should pay punitive damages. By ADOLFO PESQUERA. (To be filed in
the ``a'' and ``f'' categories.)
</P>
<P>
   The Hearst News Service/Washington
