   WASHINGTON
</P>
<P>
   EDUCATION-GORE _ WASHINGTON _ Vice President Al Gore makes what
advisers are calling the first major policy speech of his campaign
Sunday. The topic of the Iowa address is education, an issue always
near the top of voter concerns. (Mollison, Cox News Service).
Moving in (w) Washington and (p) politics categories.
</P>
<P>
   NATIONAL
</P>
<P>
   HBCU-FUNDING _ ATLANTA _ While individual contributions to
historically black colleges and universities have been up over the
last decade, they still pale in comparison to the millions given
annually to traditionally white institutions. Perhaps, said William
H. Gray, president and chief executive officer of the United Negro
College Fund, but that's not necessarily a fair comparison. (Byrd,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
