<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Your daily blast of sci-fi
 &HT;    By Staff reports
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _
</P>
<P>
   STAR STUFF
</P>
<P>
   We asked readers to tell us why they hate the Star Wars
phenomenon. Not one of you wrote in! So, we'll do it.
</P>
<P>
   Top 5 Reasons We Hate Star Wars
</P>
<P>
   1. Mark Hamill's whiny, wooden acting.
</P>
<P>
   2. Carrie Fisher's free-floating British accent.
</P>
<P>
   3. The films' contributions to the dumbing-down of cinema.
</P>
<P>
   4. We're forced to read ``serious'' articles about the religious
implications of The Farce,
</P>
<P>
   uh, we mean The Force.
</P>
<P>
   5. One word: Ewoks!
</P>
<P>
   HE'S SEEN IT ALREADY!
</P>
<P>
   Critic Hap Erstein has seen ``Phantom Menace'' _ and you
haven't! Here's his daily tidbit:
</P>
<P>
   Queen Amidala's handmaidens are so shrouded in robes that it's
hard to recognize them, but one is played by actress/director Sofia
Coppola, daughter of Francis Ford Coppola, George Lucas' old friend
and colleague.
</P>
<P>
   STAR WEB
</P>
<P>
   A weird Wars Web site: Want to check out a site with funny Star
Wars-related snapshots and Top Ten lists? Go to:
www.theforce.net/humor for a laugh.
</P>
<P>
   PHANTOM PROFILES
</P>
<P>
   JAR JAR BINKS _ This completely computerized lizard is the focal
point of the film's early criticism _ either you love the clumsy,
Disney-cute Gungan, who helps the Jedi knights on their adventure,
or you really hate him. One thing's for sure _ his ``me-sa,
you-sa'' gibberish talk is hard to understand.
</P>
<P>
   DARTH MAUL (played by Ray Park) _ He's the coolest character,
although he's on screen less than 10 minutes. He's an evil Sith who
battles the Jedi knights with a two-sided light saber. He's already
the most popular toy from the movie. When you see it, you'll know
why.
</P>
<P>
   JEDI MIND TRICKS!
</P>
<P>
   Today's Star Wars quiz
</P>
<P>
   1. The Battle of Yavin circles around the large gaseous planet
Yavin. What's the moon called that the Rebel Base is located on?
</P>
<P>
   2. What number is Luke in the Red Squadron?
</P>
<P>
   3. In ``Star Wars,'' the Yellow squad consisted of what type of
Alliance fighters?
</P>
<P>
   4. The exhaust portal on the original Death Star is as big as
what, according to Luke?
</P>
<P>
   5. What words finally persuade Han to save Princess Leia?
</P>
<P>
   Quiz answers:
</P>
<P>
   1. Yavin 42. 5
</P>
<P>
   3. Y-wings
</P>
<P>
   4. A Wamprat
</P>
<P>
   5. ``She's rich.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
