<P>
   HAWAII-BAYWATCH (Haleiwa, Hawaii) _ The biggest economic fish
caught in Hawaii this year is not a new factory or a high-tech
software start-up or a new planeload of Asian tourists, whose
financial troubles continue to keep them away in droves. No, the
biggest fish is David Hasselhoff, the head-lifeguard of
``Baywatch,'' which is to begin filming here in July, rechristened
``Baywatch Hawaii.'' By Todd S. Purdum.
</P>
<P>
   2-column hed.
</P>
<P>
   (Story has moved; `a' category.)
</P>
<P>
   2-column photo with JEFFERSON-REUNION; story is inside (skedline
below).
</P>
<P>
   WRESTLING-POLITICS (Glastonbury, Conn.) _ There may soon be a
parade of professional wrestlers who hope to duplicate last fall's
upset victory by Jesse Ventura, formerly ``the Body'' of the WWF
and now the governor of Minnesota. With huge built-in followings
and a sweaty instinct for pleasing the masses, these candidates
hope to tap voters' disgust with the same old political faces.
</P>
<P>
   1-column hed.
</P>
<P>
   (Story has moved; `a' category.)
</P>
<P>
