the Internet. U.S. District Court Judge Ricardo Urbina of
Washington, D.C., is expected this week to rule in the case. At
issue: whether the Commodity Futures Trading Commission is
trampling the rights of Web sites, newsletter publishers and
software developers that give investing advice by subjecting them
to stringent licensing procedures that include taking fingerprints
and conducting background checks. By Jon Swartz
