<TEXT>
<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following general
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
Monday, May 17, and thereafter. For questions about stories,
contact Stewart Slavin at the Daily News, (818) 713-3701.
</P>
<P>
   LA-FBI-CRIME (Los Angeles) _ The Justice Department says
preliminary figures indicate a drop in serious crime for the
seventh consecutive year. By Robert Monroe. (Will move in ``n''
California news file.)
</P>
<P>
   TOXIC-SCHOOLS (Los Angeles) _ Following promises that Los
Angeles schools would deal openly with environmental problems, new
problems at the troubled Belmont Learning Center and unauthorized
changes to legislation have led critics to charge nothing has
changed. By Greg Gittrich. (Will move in the ``n'' California news
file.)
</P>
<P>
   STARWARS-PREMIERE (Los Angeles) _ Stars of the movie ``Star
Wars: Episode 1 _ The Phantom Menace'' and other celebrities
including Magic Johnson attend a premiere in Los Angeles. By Phil
Davis. (Will move in the ``a'' national and ``n'' California news
files.)
</P>
<P>
   CELEB-CEMETERY (Los Angeles) _ The 100-year-old Hollywood
Forever cemetery, which is the final home of Douglas Fairbanks Sr.,
Rudolph Valentino and a host of other Hollywood stars, had fallen
into disrepair until last year when new owners started a
restoration project. By Steve Carney. (Will move in the ``a''
national and ``n'' California news files.)
</P>
<P>
   KITTY-COLLECTION (Glendale, Calif.) _ Welcome to all things
kitty. Cat astrology. Cat psychiatry. Cat anatomy. Cat photography.
Kitty history. Kitty litter. It's all at the Glendale Central
Library, which has the world's largest cat collection next to Yale
Library. By Donna Huffaker. (Will move in the ``a'' national and
``n'' California news files.)
</P>
<P>
   MOVIE-BOX-OFFICE (Los Angeles) _ ``The Mummy'' failed to unravel
at the nation's multiplexes over the weekend, earning $25.1 million
as the top movie at the box office, according to industry estimates
released Sunday. By Dave McNary. (Will move in the ``a'' national
and ``n'' California news files.)
