<HEADLINE>
HOLLANDWORTH DOES GOOD JOB AS UNDERSTUDY
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By MATT McHALE  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   ST. LOUIS _ When the Los Angeles Dodgers return to action
Tuesday night against the Houston Astros, Devon White is expected
to be back in center field. But Todd Hollandsworth, who started the
last six games while White was nursing a strained right hamstring,
did all the Dodgers asked.
</P>
<P>
   Not only did he go 7 for 20 during that span, including a triple
and two singles in Sunday's 5-4 loss to the St. Louis Cardinals,
Hollandsworth opened the bottom of the seventh by making a superb
running catch in right center to take away extra bases from Darren
Bragg.
</P>
<P>
   Hollandsworth's triple came in the first inning off Cardinals
starter Juan Acevedo, and he scored on a sacrifice fly by Gary
Sheffield.
</P>
<P>
   Hollandsworth, the Dodgers opening-day left fielder the previous
three seasons, is strictly coming off the bench these days. To make
it worse, he missed most of the first month with a strained left
hamstring.
</P>
<P>
   ``Baseball is a game of rhythm, getting a feeling on the bases,
at the plate and in the field,'' said Hollandsworth, who now is
batting .294 (10 for 34). ``These last few games have given me a
chance to get that back, but I have no illusions that this means
I'll play any more than I am.
</P>
<P>
   ``What it does do is let them know that they can put me out
there and know that I'll do the job.''
</P>
<P>
   __ Day of rest: Hollandsworth wasn't the only bench player to
start Sunday. The Dodgers went with Paul LoDuca behind the plate in
place of Todd Hundley, Dave Hansen instead of Eric Karros at first
and Jose Vizcaino at third for Adrian Beltre.
</P>
<P>
   After Saturday night's 8-5 loss, manger Davey Johnson told
Beltre, who came in with a .333 (19 for 57) average in his last 16
games, that he wasn't starting. Jose Vizcaino started at third, but
Beltre entered the game in the third after Vizcaino left with a
strained muscle behind the left knee and went 0 for 2. Vizcaino
will be examined today.
</P>
<P>
   LoDuca went 0 for 4 and is batting .056 (2 for 36) with no home
runs or RBI. Hansen, the team's top pinch hitter, went 1 for 2 with
a run and is batting .462 (12 for 26) with two homers and five RBI.
</P>
<P>
   __ Brown goes home: The Dodgers flew back after the game and are
off today before opening a three-game series against Houston at
Dodger Stadium. They play the Cardinals again this weekend for the
final time this season.
</P>
<P>
   Kevin Brown, who will pitch Wednesday, flew back to his home in
Macon, Ga., after Sunday's game. He used a plane provided by Fox,
as part of the seven-year, $105 million contract signed last
winter.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
